{
  "texts": [
    "In terms of chloride penetration, WGP at a 15% replacement ratio achieves the greatest reduction, about 50%, indicating its strong capability to prevent chloride ingress.",
    "FA at a 25% replacement ratio also shows considerable effectiveness in reducing chloride penetration.",
    "Meanwhile, SCBA and Zeolite, both at a 15% replacement level, offer moderate improvements.",
    "POFA at a 10% replacement ratio and GGBFS at 30% present lower levels of improvement but still provide some resistance to chloride penetration.",
    "On the other hand, Shrinkage resistance is one of the important properties must be discuss which is a deformation process that reduces the cross-section and dimensions of cement-based materials, often resulting in cracks."
  ]
}